==English==

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''pan and scan'''

#The method or practice of adjusting [[widescreen]] film images so that they can shown within the proportions of a 1.33:1 [[aspect ratio]] television screen, by cropping off sides of the original widescreen image, as opposed to [[letterboxing]].

====Translations====
*[[Japanese]]: [[鍋及びスキャン]] (nabeoyobi-sukyan)
*[[Korean]]: [[팬과 검사]] (paengwa geomsa)

===Adjective===
'''pan-and-scan'''

#Formatted to fit within proportions of a 1.33:1 aspect ratio television screen, with sides of the original widescreen image cropped off.  

===Verb===
'''to pan and scan'''

#To adjust (widescreen film images) so that they can be shown within the proportions of a 1.33:1 aspect ratio telvision screen, by cropping off sides of the original widescreen image.

''On the fullscreen version of Star Wars Episode II, only Anakin and Obi-Wan appear on the scene, but Padmé was '''panned and scanned''' out of the scene.''

